  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CPB device operates continuously in vivo during cardiac surgery procedures lasting 2–8 hours under perfusionist supervision; the pump head is subject to bearing wear, seal degradation, and motor drive voltage fluctuation over the course of an extended bypass run. All validation activities and CFD simulations assume nominal hardware in factory-calibrated condition; no fault states are represented in the model or experimental campaign.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
