      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs extracted from the model (RH index, volume-averaged shear stress) must be directly traceable to the clinical hemolysis acceptance criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed directly from CFD-derived shear stress and exposure time fields using the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law model. RH is the regulatory QoI used in predicate device comparison. Traceability to clinical outcome is established through published correlation with plasma-free hemoglobin measurements."
    },
    {
