      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for viscosity (±10%), inlet turbulence intensity (1%–5%), and rotational speed (±50 RPM). RH is most sensitive to rotational speed (±6% RH per ±50 RPM). All inputs set to nominal design values; degraded hardware inputs (e.g., increased bearing friction torque, reduced impeller clearance due to wear) were not included in the sensitivity study."
