    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient predictive credibility for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions across the nominal clinical flow-speed envelope. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied for all evaluated configurations relative to the predicate device. The assessment team notes that all validation activities were conducted on factory-new, geometrically nominal hardware under controlled bench conditions, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. The model is accepted for the stated COU.",
